event_title_eng: Forms of communal living in Berlin
event_desc_eng:
Panel discussion on different forms of communal living.

This discussion will take place as part of this year‚Äôs coworking festival Berlin, our aim is to broaden the discussion to include different ways of living as well as work; those who share their working space tend to be open to sharing their living space too.

Cohousing, coliving, podliving, cooperatives, tiny house communities ‚Äì these are all are forms of communal living that are getting more and more popular for people from various age groups, cultural, and social backgrounds.

During this discussion we will analyze the different types of communal living, the motives behind them, their main challenges, and their future prospects; all from people who are building the scene right now in Berlin.

If you are living communally, coliving and/ or coworking, using different sharing economy platforms, we would love to have your input.

If you are curious about living communally in Berlin this is the right place to start as well.

Panel speakers:

‚Ä¢  Tobias Brockmann; Co-founder of Happy Pigeons Coliving and Forever Day One
‚Ä¢  Naima Ritter; a Conscious Living Coach and sustainable development professional
‚Ä¢  A representative from a tiny house community ( TBC )
‚Ä¢  A representative from a Baugroup ( TBC )
‚Ä¢  A representative from a co-housing community (TBC)

Program

6:00 PM: Doors open, informal networking
6:30 PM: Panel discussion
8:00 PM: Open audience discussion

‚Ä¢ Coliving

event_title_eng: Strategy Meetup: Startup Marketing Done Right!
event_desc_eng:
The "Go-To-Market"-Phase is the most crucial for any business, product or service. Get this right and experience exponential growth!

Starting a product, service or a buiness based on an idea is easy compared to finding customers who really want to buy! On top of having a product or a service according to someones needs or requirements it is crucial to have the right approach and strategy to leverage such a a feature set.

On Sep. 10th, 2019, at 6pm we will have our initial meetup on Startup marketing and Business Strategy. During the event you will learn the following:

‚Ä¢  When is the right time to care about marketing & sales
‚Ä¢  What is the right process and tools for finding potential customers
‚Ä¢  How can you easily transform your business towards growth
‚Ä¢  How can you leverage a minimum product / service feature
‚Ä¢  What skills does your team need in order to make business growth reality?

The session will include short introductions to each topic and experience from business owners. There will also time for getting to know each other and to expand your network.

Sebastian Eumann has been in Sales and Marketing Management for many years. Sebastian has led many cross funtional Sales teams towards success. Additionally he has many years of experience in Business Development for international technology companies and startups. With his expertise he has managed many change processes in the organizations he has worked with. Sebastian's passion is to motivate individuals and teams and make them aware of their own strengths so that they are capable for growth, connection and purpose.

event_desc_eng:

To be conscious and sustainable when consuming‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs the new way to be! But what exactly does it mean to be conscious and how do you recognise fair clothes?

Assunta Crux is the founder of fineyellow, a marketplace for fair and sustainable fashion. Visiting this workshop is your smooth and easy start into becoming a conscious consumer. Come as a beginner, leave as a pro!

event_title_eng: Community lunch for future: Creating eco-friendly workspaces
event_desc_eng:
Coworking Spaces are the work spaces of the present and future. They provide infrastructure and community for people with various needs and backgrounds. That's what makes them so great. But the different cultures and habits of people also make it challenging for spaces to be eco-friendly.

Let's brainstorm:

‚Ä¢  How can we create spaces where everyone respects the environment?
‚Ä¢  How are these spaces designed?
‚Ä¢  How can we reduce waste and build a local network of service providers?
‚Ä¢  How can spaces support each other in becoming sustainable?

The session will be accompanied by a homemade vegan lunch.
